questions.question:
Consider an array X that contains positive integers. A subarray of X is defined to be a sequence of array locations with consecutive indices. The code snippet given below has been written to compute the length of the longest subarray of X that contains at most two distinct integers. The code has two missing expressions labelled (P) and (Q).

int lm1 = 1, lm2 = 1, lm3 = 1, max = 1;
first = X[0]; second = -1;
for (i = 1; i <= n-1; i++) {
    if (X[i] == first || X[i] == second) {
        lm1 = lm1 + 1;
    } else {
        second = first;
        first = X[i];
        lm2 = (P);
        lm1 = lm2 + 1;
    }
    lm3 = lm1;
    if (lm3 > max) max = lm3;
}

Which one of the following options gives the CORRECT missing expressions?

A. (P) |lm1| + 1   (Q) lm2 + 1
B. (P) 1            (Q) lm1 + 1
C. (P) lm3 + 1      (Q) lm1 + 1
D. (P) lm1 + 1      (Q) lm2 + 1
